<HEADLINE> Downhill Races Scheduled for Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVE, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The final men's and women's World
Cup downhill Alpine ski races this season have been postponed to
Friday because of fog in Crans-Montana, Switzerland, on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Reports said four speed events will be raced on Friday in a
World Cup first.
</P>
<P>
The downhill races will be held before men's and women's Super
G events.
</P>
<P>
Double Olympic champion Katja Seizinger of Germany has already
won the women's downhill title and Austria's Andreas Schifferer
has claimed the men's downhill. 
</P>
</TEXT>
