<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Rise on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to rise
on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index (STII) picked up marginally by three points to close at
1580.84 Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Property stocks emerged the top gainers. However, dealers said
investors remained sidelined pending further developments in
Indonesia and the local corporate scene.
</P>
<P>
Share prices in the broader market moved sideways for most of
the day as investors took stock of recent gains and appeared to
exercise some caution, they said.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume shrank to 195.75 million units, valued at
331.68 million Singapore dollars (204.74 million U.S. dollars).
Declines led advances by 168 to 152, while 293 other counters
remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Renong Bhd continued to be the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 13.72 million units. It was followed by
MBf Capital which had 8.45 million shares traded. Rekapac was next
with 8.2 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Property developer City Developments Warrant98 and Khong Guan
shared the top spot on the gainers' list as each of them rose by
50 cents to finish at 4.98 and five Singapore dollars
respectively. City Developments, Creative 50 and DBS (Development
Bank of Singapore) all increased by 40 cents to end at 7.65, 37.1,
and 9.2 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Elec was the biggest loser as it declined by
40 cents to close at 5.6 U.S. dollars. Local car distributor Cycle
&AMP; Carriage (C&AMP;C), SIA (Singapore Airlines) Foreign, and Venture
fell by 20 cents each to finish at 6.75, 11.4, and 5.7 Singapore
dollars respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
