<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada's Vehicle Sales Drop Sharply in January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, March 12 (Xinhua) -- New motor vehicle sales in Canada
fell sharply in January following strong sales in December,
Statistics Canada reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Total vehicle sales plunged 27.0 percent to 105,595 from the high
of 144,555 in December. "The month-to-month sales decrease was the
largest drop since January 1976," the statistics agency said.
</P>
<P>
In January, a total of 50,689 passenger cars were sold in the
country, down 24.1 percent from a month before.
</P>
<P>
Sales of trucks, vans and buses fell 29.4 percent to 54,906 in
January.
</P>
<P>
"Industry sources have suggested that dealers might have drawn
some business into December by offering customers strong incentives
on the purchase of new motor vehicles," the agency said.
</P>
<P>
"This shift in sales, coupled with the January ice storm,
contributed to a substantial decline in new vehicles sales in
January," it noted.
</P>
<P>
However, on a year-over-year basis, Canada's new vehicle sales were
0.7 percent ahead of January 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
