<HEADLINE> Identification Resumes in Western Sahara </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The identification of
people eligible to participate in a referendum on the future of
Western Sahara has resumed, U.N. spokesman Eckhard said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Announcing the resumption of the process, which had been
suspended since February 27, Eckhard said some differences between
the Popular Front for the Liberation of Saguia el-Hamra and Rio De
Oro (POLISALIO Front) and Morocco over the contested tribes had
prevented the adoption of the March program for the
identification.
</P>
<P>
