<HEADLINE> German Auto Output Up 8 Percent in February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The Frankfurt-based German
Automobile Federation (VDA) Thursday said that the country's
automobile output totaled 445,440 vehicles in February, up 8
percent over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
This was compared with a 4 percent drop in January.
</P>
<P>
According to the VDA, passenger car output rose by 7 percent to
414,600 units thanks to stronger domestic demand. Truck production
surged 12 percent to 30,800 units.
</P>
<P>
It reported a 5 percent rise in domestic orders for cars, and a
14 percent rise in that for trucks.
</P>
<P>
Germany exported 242,900 cars last month, an increase of 4
percent over February 1997, while truck exports were up 9 percent.
</P>
