<HEADLINE> Zanzibar to Build New Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Construction of the much
awaited Zanzibar Modern Market estimated to cost about 700,000 U.S.
Dollars is expected to start next Monday, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Mayor of the Zanzibar Municipal Council, Mwaulid Salum, told
reporters Thursday that the market will be able to accommodate some
3,000 petty traders and have telecommunication and sanitary facilities.
</P>
<P>
The new market will be built at Mwanakwerekwe area, close to
Zanzibar's well-known tourist destination Stone Town, Salum said.
</P>
<P>
The project, funded by the National Income Generating Program
(NIGP), is scheduled to be completed by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
The old Darajani market, which was built in 1920s with few
space for petty traders, has become unable to meet the demand of
the fast growing population in the Zanzibar isles. That during
the rain season, overflowing cesspits pose as a nuisance to local
residents and tourists.
</P>
<P>
The Zanzibar Municipal Council will take charge of the new market
including collection of revenue, the mayor said.  
</P>
