<HEADLINE> People's Immediate Interests Focus of NPC, CPPCC Sessions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang has specifically warned against "hastily pushing the
workers to the society," at the time when China's social security
system still has much to improve.
</P>
<P>
On hearing that farmers were still being arbitrarily charged
with non-warranted fees, Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji, who have always
concerned himself with the financial burdens imposed on farmers,
scathingly said, "how can those have the heart" to throw such
heavy burdens on farmers, whose income are low and some of whom
are still living in dire poverty.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, reelected chairman of the CPPCC National Committee,
noted that the interests of the people should be taken into full
account when local governments are working out development schemes
and working plans and at media coverage.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few days, the media have released a host of
reports on how the central leading officials show solicitude
for the people.
</P>
<P>
As the NPC session entered the second stage, related issues,
such as anti-corruption, public security and the development of
cultural and ethic progress, have become the focus of attention by
NPC deputies and members.
</P>
<P>
When approving of the achievements made by the government,
judicial departments and law-enforcing organs in their endeavor to
combat corruption and crimes, deputies and members have voiced the
hope that more effective measures should be adopted to create
still better conditions for the reform, opening up and
modernization, as well as a better working and living environment
for the public.
</P>
<P>
Many NPC deputies and CPPCC members have criticized some local
officials' false practices, with some CPPCC members advocating the
that related problems be dealt with by law.
</P>
<P>
Among the moves, proposals, and suggestions put forth by
deputies and members, many are on issues with which people are generally
concerned.
</P>
<P>
Attending a panel discussion earlier, Tian Jiyun, secretary
general of the current NPC session, demanded that the deputies
report truthfully on the feelings and aspirations of the people
and the criticisms and suggestions they set forth on the work of
governments at all levels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
