<HEADLINE> Qian Zhengying, Vice-Chairman of Ninth CPPCC National Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Qian, Female, of Han Nationality, born in Jiaxing, Zhejiang
Province, in July 1923, joined Communist Party of China (CPC) and
started work in Sept. 1941, graduated from Department of Civil
Engineering of Datong University in Shanghai, academician of
Academy of Engineering of China.
</P>
<P>
Served as vice-minister and minister in charge of Water
Resources, and Water Conservancy and Power.
</P>
<P>
Elected member of 10th through 14th CPC Central Committees, as
well as vice-chairwoman of 7th and 8th CPPCC National Committees.
</P>
