<HEADLINE> World Cup Men's Downhill Standings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVE, Mar 13 (Xinhua) -- Following are the final men's World
Cup downhill standings after Friday's race in Crans Montana,
Switzerland:
</P>
<P>
1. Andreas Schifferer, Austria, 655 points
</P>
<P>
2. Herman Maier, Austria, 479
</P>
<P>
3. Nicolas Burtin, France, 469
</P>
<P>
4. Didier Cuche, Switzerland, 424
</P>
<P>
5. Jean-Luc Cretier, France, 414
</P>
