<HEADLINE> 30 Feared Dead in Landslide in Pak-Controlled Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 13 (Xinhua) -- At least 30 people were feared
dead and many others injured Friday as a result of a massive
landslide at Reshian in Leepa Valley, about 50 kilometers from
Muzaffarabad, capital of Pakistan-controlled Kashmir area.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here Friday afternoon said that torrent mud
and rocks triggered by a landslide caused 30 houses to cave in,
leaving at least 30 dead, including 10 women. 
