<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French Plane Repair Company Expects Closer Ties with China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Messier-Bugatti, a plane parts
production and repair company of France, wishes to reinforce
cooperation with China in technological service and personnel
training, said the company's president Yves Leclere on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Leclere said at a press conference that since establishing a
bureau in Beijing in 1997, Messier-Bugatti has been doing very
well in China by providing services in repairing Airbus and Boeing
planes, bought by China in large quantities.
</P>
<P>
Messier-Bugatti, which is also one of the world's three largest
producers of wheels and airbrakes, braking systems, landing
systems and hydraulics used on Airbus and Boeing planes, plans to
establish a permanent service for technical support and
distribution of spare parts for the Airbus planes in China, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Leclere expected the next five years to be full of "economic
wars in plane service industries," and said that his company will
be ready to offer "total and guaranteed service," especially in
repairing and renewing braking systems and landing systems of
planes.
</P>
<P>
Messier-Bugatti has an annual sales volume of 1.614 billion
francs (270 million U.S. dollars) and spends 147 million francs
(24.5 million U.S. dollars) in research projects each year.
</P>
</TEXT>
