<HEADLINE> Chirac Confident About Future of Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 13 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac on
Friday expressed confidence in the future of Hong Kong under the
"one country, two systems" policy when meeting Tung Chee-hwa,
Chief Executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR) of China.
</P>
<P>
During the one-hour meeting at the Elysee presidential palace,
Chirac described the relations between France and the HKSAR as
"excellent," against a background of overall good relations
between France and China, said sources at the presidential palace.
</P>
<P>
The close relations between France and the HKSAR were also
important because of the "absolute necessity to reinforce the
Euro-Asia relations," said Chirac.
</P>
<P>
Tung expressed his appreciation to Chirac for his support, and
said Hong Kong will not abandon the currency board which pegs the
Hong Kong dollar to the U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
The stability of both the Chinese yuan (Renminbi) and the Hong
Kong dollar is very important for financial stability in Asia,
Tung said.
</P>
<P>
Chirac agreed with Tung that "Asia has all the trumps to face
up to the financial crisis."
</P>
<P>
Tung invited Chirac to visit Hong Kong at a time of his
convenience.
</P>
<P>
Chirac said he had planned to visit Hong Kong in May 1997, but
had to abandon the plan because of an early legislative election
at home.
</P>
<P>
Tung ended his three-day visit to France on later Friday and
left here for home. 
</P>
</TEXT>
