<HEADLINE> Poorest Region Expects to Shake Off Poverty by 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Xihaigu, the poorest area in the
under-developed northwestern Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region,
expects to shake off poverty by the end of the century, according
to a regional leader.
</P>
<P>
"We will use every means possible to shake off poverty in
Xihaigu and I can assure you that it will not drag down the
country's poverty-reducing progress," said Ma Qizhi, chairman of
the regional government at a news conference hosed here today by
the on-going session of the National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
Inhabited by 2.2 million Muslims, Xihaigu is known as the
hardest nut to crack in China's poverty elimination program due to
its extremely harsh environment and chronic drought.
</P>
<P>
Despite a drop in poor population in the area over recent
years, it still has some 520,000 people who can barely feed and
clothe themselves.
</P>
<P>
According to Ma, great efforts will be made to improve basic
farming and living conditions in poverty-stricken areas. A water
diverting project, funded by the central government, has been
diverting water from the Yellow River to the arid land in Xihaigu.
</P>
<P>
By the year 2000, about 30,000 hectares of waste land will be
turned into erable land where the last group of the poor people in
mountainous areas will be relocated, Ma said.
</P>
<P>
Ma revealed the central government allocates some 30 million
yuan in poverty relieving funds each year to the region. The water
diversion project cost a total of 3 billion yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
