<HEADLINE> Yeltsin's Ailment Drops Russian Markets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Russian markets fell slightly on
Friday after reports that President Boris Yeltsin was undergoing
medical treatment for an acute respiratory infection.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin, 67, canceled his meetings Friday and was undergoing
treatment at his Gorky-9 residence after doctors said he was
suffering from an acute respiratory infection, the Interfax news
agency quoted presidential spokesman Sergei Yastrzhembsky as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Russian blue chips dropped by two percent following the news of
Yeltsin's ailment.
</P>
<P>
The Russian Trading System said that within the first half hour
of Friday's trading, its own index fell by 1.9 percent from
Thursday closing, and its technical index was down by 1.49 percent.
</P>
<P>
A senior trader said the index started falling as soon as
traders heard the news.
</P>
<P>
Another trader said the news of Yeltsin's illness had a far
bigger impact on the markets than the interest cut by the Central
Bank of Russia. 
</P>
