<HEADLINE> Chairman of CPPCC National Committee Reelected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan was reelected chairman
of the Ninth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC) this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The result came from the fifth plenary meeting of the First
Session of the Ninth CPPCC National Committee held here today.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, 63, is also a Standing Committee member of the
Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central
Committee.
</P>
<P>
He was elected chairman of the CPPCC National Committee for the
first time in March 1993 at the First Session of the Eighth CPPCC
National Committee.
</P>
<P>
The CPPCC is the most extensive patriotic united front
organization in China, with its main functions to exercise
political consultation, democratic supervision and participation
in the discussion and deliberation of state affairs.
</P>
<P>
The Ninth National Committee has a total of 2,195 members,
2,048 of whom attended the plenum today.
</P>
<P>
The lists of candidates for chairman, vice-chairmen,
secretary-general and Standing Committee members of the Ninth
CPPCC National Committee were submitted to the plenary meeting
following ample discussions and deliberations in various CPPCC
panels for approval of the presidium of 1st Session of the
Ninth CPPCC National Committee. And the lists were set forth for
voting at the plenum today.
</P>
<P>
According to the Constitution of the CPPCC, the candidates for
chairman, vice-chairmen, secretary-general and Standing Committee
members of the CPPCC National Committee are nominated by various
parties, organizations, ethnic groups, social quarters and figures
from various walks of life joining the CPPCC National Committee,
and elected by a plenum of the CPPCC National Committee.
</P>
<P>
Presided over by Wang Zhaoguo, executive chairman of the
presidium, the election this afternoon was carried out by
secret ballot.
</P>
<P>
The election of chairman, vice-chairmen, secretary-general and
Standing Committee members were conducted through
one-candidate-for-one-post method and, they could be elected
provided that they got more than half of the votes.
</P>
<P>
At about 4:00 PM today, the chairman, 31 vice-chairmen, one
secretary-general and 290 Standing Committee members of the CPPCC
Ninth National Committee were elected, at the presence of 48
scrutineers with Bai Keming and Li Ruiying as scrutineers-general.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
