<HEADLINE> Ngapoi Ngawang Jigme, Vice-Chairman of Ninth CPPCC National Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Following is a biographical
sketch of Ngapoi Ngawang Jigme, who was reelected vice-chairman of
the Ninth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC).
</P>
<P>
Ngapoi, born Feb. 1910, native Tibetan of Lhasa, Tibet.
</P>
<P>
Served as a grain supplies official in Qamdo Prefecture and
civil magistrate and auditor or "Kasha", in Tibet local
government, 1936-52.
</P>
<P>
He went to Beijing and signed an accord with central government
on peaceful liberation of Tibet in as chief negotiator of Tibet
local government in 1951.
</P>
<P>
Severed as first deputy commander of the Tibet Military
Areas Command, secretary-general and deputy director of the
Preparatory Committee of the Tibet Autonomous Region, 1952-59.
</P>
<P>
Served as vice-chairman of the CPPCC National Committee,
vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress (NPC) and deputy director of the Preparatory Committee of
of the Tibet Autonomous Region, 1959-64.
</P>
<P>
Served as vice-chairman of National People's Congress (NPC)
Standing Committee and chairman of Tibet Autonomous Regional
government, 1965-79.
</P>
<P>
Served as vice-chairman of NPC Standing Committee, chairman of
NPC Ethnic Affairs Committee, chairman of Tibet Autonomous
Regional NPC Standing Committee, as well as chairman of the Tibet
regional government, 1979-93.
</P>
<P>
He was vice-chairman of 1st, 3rd and 8th CPPCC National
Committees, deputy to the 1st through 7th NPCs, vice-chairman of
of the Standing Committee of the 3rd through 7th NPCs and chairman
of the NPC Ethnic Affairs Committee of the 5th through 7th NPCs.
