<HEADLINE> Chinese President on Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
today stressed the importance of continuing to develop agriculture
as the country's economic base at a group discussion attended by
Henan deputies to the National People's Congress, in session here
since early March.
</P>
<P>
Jiang urged Henan, China's most popular province and a leading
grain producer, to deepen reforms, expand the scope of opening and
accelerate economic development, thus making greater contributions
to the nation.
</P>
<P>
Jiang focused on agriculture at the discussion.
</P>
<P>
"We should unswervingly adhere to the principle of taking
agriculture as the foundation of the national economy," he said.
</P>
<P>
He cautioned people not to slacken work in the wake of good
grain harvests for several consecutive years to prevent a decline
in grain production.
</P>
<P>
"We can't say, at any time, that there is too much grain and
relax our efforts at grain production," he said.
</P>
<P>
To ensure a sustained and steady agricultural development,
rural communities must launch farming-oriented capital
construction projects, and improve production conditions and the
ecological environment, he said.
</P>
<P>
Efforts should be made to harness rivers by building more water
conservancy projects, he said.
</P>
<P>
In view of worsening water shortages in north China, Li called
on local people to develop water-efficient farming, plant more
grass and trees and control sand encroachment.
</P>
<P>
Jiang urged leading officials to protect the enthusiasm of
farmers, alleviate their burdens, stabilize the land contract
system and promote democracy in rural areas by setting up
democratic election systems and making public village account
books.  
</P>
</TEXT>
