<HEADLINE> Jiang Urged Local Governments to Support Institutional Restructuring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin today urged
local governments across the country to give full support to the
forthcoming institutional restructuring of the State Council,
China's cabinet, and make preparations for their own institutional
reforms.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made these remarks in a panel discussion with deputies
from north China's Hebei Province to the Ninth National People's
Congress (NPC), top Chinese legislature, in session here since
early March.
</P>
<P>
The current NPC session approved the State Council's
institutional restructuring plan last Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"Government downsizing, which will affect powers of various
departments and personal interests of all officials, is an arduous
task that will have an impact on the overall situation of reform,
development and stability," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
While realizing the necessity and urgency of institutional
restructuring, it is also necessary to make careful arrangements
and take the overall situation into account, to ensure ideological
unity and a good order and consistency of government work, he
noted.
</P>
<P>
"Local governments at all levels must actively support the
institutional restructuring of the State Council, and be well
prepared to push forward their own institutional reforms according
to the general arrangements of the State Council," he urged.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that it is very important to improve the
building of democracy and a legal system and maintain social and
political stability.
</P>
<P>
"It is necessary to create a stable social and political
environment for reform and development through the promotion of
the rule of law," he said.
</P>
<P>
A fundamental way to implement the principle of administering
the country according to law is to make greater efforts in
legislation, law enforcement, administration of justice and spread
of legal knowledge, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he said, the public security situation must be
improved through a quick and severe crackdown according to law on
serious crimes harming social and economic order.
</P>
<P>
He also called for intensified efforts to spread legal
knowledge across the country.
</P>
<P>
"I always believe that while it's important to enhance the
legal awareness of the general public, it's more critical to
improve the legal awareness of officials, especially leading
officials, and their ability to do everything in accordance with
law," he noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
