<HEADLINE> Amnesty For More Than Five Million South Koreans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The South Korean government on
Friday granted a sweeping amnesty to 5.5 million law-breakers, the
biggest general pardon since the founding of the country in 1948.
</P>
<P>
Of those set free by the amnesty, which was approved by the
cabinet council at an extraordinary session, are 5.32 million
violators of traffic laws.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the remaining prison terms of 31,487 criminals will
be waived, and the revoked rights of 806 people will be restored.
</P>
<P>
The amnesty also includes more than 166,000 public workers,
whose records of reprimand will be erased from their files.
</P>
</TEXT>
