<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eastern Chinese Province's Environmental Protection Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, March 13 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang Province
has begun a "Love Our Common Home" campaign to increase awareness
of the importance of environmental protection, according to Zhang
Hongming, director of the Provincial Environmental Protection
Bureau, who made the announcement here today.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang is one of China's most developed provinces and places
great significance on environmental protection, he said. The
government has made it part of its long-term economic and social
development plan and local governments have been asked to play a
greater role in implementing local environmental protection
programs.
</P>
<P>
The Provincial Environmental Protection Project began in June
1994, and Zhejiang has set up 127 smoke and dust control zones on
a 900-sq.km. area, cleaned 148 cement factories, opened a
150-sq.km. low-noise area, established 141 water-source protection
zones, made 104 villages and towns ecologically friendly, and
brought 128 major pollution sources under control.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to these efforts, the amount of pollutants discharged
has not risen at a rate similar to that of economic growth in the
province, Zhang said, and to improve the environment more, the
province will build a number of model cities and prefectures, so
that by the end of the century, environmental pollution in the
province will be brought under control. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
