<HEADLINE> ARATS Official Calls For Increasing Cross-Strait Contacts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese official called
for increasing contacts between the Beijing-based Association For
Relations Across the Taiwan Straits (Arats) and the Straits
Exchange Foundation (Sef)in Taiwan with a view to narrowing
differences.
</P>
<P>
"Arats and Sef share some views and have some differences over
topics for discussion in future talks, therefore the major task
for the two bodies now is to seek common ground by increasing
contacts and exchanges," said Arats Vice Chairman Tang Shubei.
</P>
<P>
Tang talked about impending talks between Arats and Sef at a
panel discussion yesterday attended by members of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference, in session here since early March.
</P>
<P>
As to topics for discussion, Tang said, it is the stand of
Arats that arrangements should first be made on procedural matters
relating to ending cross-Strait hostilities and resume economic
and business talks.
</P>
<P>
He said Arats is actively promoting contacts and exchanges with
Sef and hopes the two sides can hold informal talks on topics for
discussion and making arrangements for Sef chairman Koo Chen-fu's
visit to the mainland.
</P>
<P>
Tang reiterated that the "one China" principle must be upheld
in handling across-Strait affairs as well as in talks between the
two sides. 
</P>
</TEXT>
