<HEADLINE> Zheng Wantong, CPPCC Ninth National Committee Secretary-General </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Following is a biographical
sketch of Zheng Wantong, who was elected general-secretary of the
Ninth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC).
</P>
<P>
Born May, 1941; native of Tianjin; joined Communist Party of
China (CPC) August, 1960; started work in August, 1961.
</P>
<P>
After graduating from Chinese Language Department of Tianjin
Teachers' College in 1961, Zheng taught at No.78 Middle School in
Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
Was head of School Work Department of Communist Youth League of
China (CYLC) Hebei District Committee in Tianjin from 1965 to
1968.
</P>
<P>
Worked as a cadre and later deputy head of Publicity Department
of CPC Hebei District Committee of Tianjin from 1970 to 1978.
</P>
<P>
Worked as a cadre at General Office and Policy Study Office of
CPC Tianjin Municipal Committee from 1978 to 1982. Was director of
General Office from 1982 to 1983, secretary-general of Municipal
Committee from 1983 to 1988.
</P>
<P>
From 1988 to 1993, was vice-chairman of Executive Committee of
All-China Federation of Trade Unions.
</P>
<P>
From 1993 to the election this afternoon, was deputy head of
United Front Work Department of CPC Central Committee, deputy
secretary-general and Standing Committee member of CPPCC Eighth
National Committee.
</P>
<P>
Has been member of CPC Central Commission for Discipline
Inspection since 15th National Congress of CPC convened in fall of
1997. 
</P>
