<HEADLINE> Train Rams on Truck in Thailand, Killing 11 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 13 (Xinhua) -- At least 11 people were killed
and six others seriously injured in a traffic accident Friday when
a train ran into a truck in a railway junction in Thailand's
northeastern province of Chaiyaphum, local television reported
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred at 7:45 a.m. local time (0045 GMT) Friday
when the truck passed the junction without noticing the coming
train.
</P>
<P>
Nine people aboard the truck were immediately killed when it
was violently hit by the train and crashed to pieces.
</P>
<P>
Another eight people on the truck were seriously wounded and
sent to a nearby hospital after the accident. Two of them died in
the hospital later.
</P>
<P>
People aboard the truck are said to go to a wedding party.
</P>
</TEXT>
