Switzerland, after American Nagano Olympic Super-G champion Picabo
Street crashed in the race.
</P>
<P>
The much-delayed race was first suspended to allow Street, the
second starter, to be taken off the mountain by helicopter to the
hospital after her crashing high up on the Nationale piste with a
knee injury.
</P>
<P>
She also crashed heavily in the last World Cup downhill in Are,
Sweden, in January just before the Olympics.
</P>
<P>
The organizers decided to call off the final competition for
unsafe to continue.
</P>
<P>
The cancellation meant Germany's double Nagano Olympic champion
Katja Seizinger of Germany took the overall World Cup title.
</P>
<P>
Both men's and women's Super-G races were cancelled because of
fog but a men's downhill was finished. 
