<HEADLINE> Yang Rudai, Vice-Chairman of Ninth CPPCC National Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Following is a biographical
sketch of Yang Rudai, who was just elected today vice-chairman of
the Ninth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC).
</P>
<P>
Yang, born in 1926, native of Renshou, Sichuan Province,
jointed Communist Party of China (CPC) in 1952, received
equivalent high-school education..
</P>
<P>
Did youth work and took charge of it, and joined a land reform
team in native county, 1950-54, worked as deputy head of the
Organizational Department of CPC Renshou County Committee,
1954-56, deputy secretary and secretary of CPC Renshou County
Committee, 1956-76.
</P>
<P>
Promoted to the post of secretary of CPC Leshan Prefecture
Committee in Sichuan, 1977-78, and served as vice-governor of
Sichuan Province, member of the secretariat of CPC Sichuan
provincial committee and executive secretary of the CPC provincial
committee, 1978-83.
</P>
<P>
Stayed as Sichuan Provincial Party Secretary, 1983-87; and
served as member of the Political Bureau of CPC Central Committee
and secretary of the CPC Sichuan Provincial Committee, 1987-92;
and secretary of the CPC Sichuan Provincial Committee, 1992-93.
</P>
<P>
He has been vice-chairman of CPPCC National Committee and
member of the Party Group of CPPCC National Committee since 1993,
</P>
<P>
Yang was member of the 12th and 13th CPC Central Committees and
member of the Political Bureau of the 13th CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Yang was elected vice-chairman of the Eighth CPPCC National
Committee.  
</P>
