<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading French newspapers Friday.
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- A high-level delegation of the Serbian government, carrying
proposals of dialogue with ethnic Albanians, arrived Thursday in
Pristina, capital of Kosovo, without being able to meet political
representatives of the Albanians.
</P>
<P>
-- French President Jacques Chirac Thursday threatened to block
the process of admitting Cyprus by the European Union, if only the
northern Greek Cyprus is accepted by the EU. "The European Union
does not have the right to take a piece of Cyprus and thus
integrate a conflict which is not its own," said Chirac at the
European Conference held in London. Meanwhile, Turkey has accused
the EU of creating a new Yalta structure by dividing the Muslim
world from the Christian world in Europe.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- The opposition Rally for the Republic and Union for French
Democracy will have a close fight with the Socialist Party in the
Paris region, or Il-de-France, and the southern
Provence-Alpes-Cote d'Azur, where the big cities of Marseille and
Nice are located. In both of the two regions, the shifting of
the votes for the far-right National Front will be decisive for
winning the presidency of regional parliaments on March 15.
</P>
<P>
-- The crisis in Kosovo dominated the agenda of the first
meeting of the European Conference held in London on Thursday,
which gathered the "great European family" from 15 EU countries
and 11 candidate countries for EU membership. The 26 countries
condemned "with great vehemence" the resort to "excessive force"
by the government of Belgrade against ethnic Albanians, and called
for an upgrading of the statute for Kosovo within the Yugoslav
federation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
