<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tibetans Mark Anniversary Of Birth Of China's Premier Zhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Some 100 local officials and common
folk gathered today in Lhasa, the capital of the Tibet
Autonomous Region, for the 100th anniversary of the birth of
Premier Zhou Enlai.
</P>
<P>
People who had met Zhou, who was the People's Republic's first
premier, praised Zhou for his profound love of the Tibetan people.
</P>
<P>
The deputy director of the Regional Cultural Department, Suona,
recalled that in 1963 when she was a young girl serving as a
member of the Regional Military Command Troupe, the premier had
taught her how to dance, and although he never visited Tibet, he
lives in the hearts of Tibetans.
</P>
<P>
Those at the gathering said that in the first years of New
China, Zhou and other members of the earlier generation of
revolutionaries worked out a series of pragmatic policies and
principles to develop the economy of Tibet, laying a foundation
for development of the autonomous region.
</P>
<P>
They pledged to fight against any sabotage by hostile
forces, to safeguard the unity of the motherland, and oppose
divisiveness. 
</P>
</TEXT>
