<HEADLINE> 6 Philippine Presidential Candidates Sign Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Six of the 11 presidential
candidates in the Philippines Friday signed a covenant that aims
at keeping the coming elections peaceful, orderly and honest.
</P>
<P>
The covenant was drawn up by the Commission on Elections.
</P>
<P>
The six who signed the covenant include former defense
secretary Renato de Villa, Manila Mayor Alfredo Lim and former
first lady Imelda Marcos.
</P>
<P>
Those who failed to ink the document include Vice President
Joseph Estrada who has been leading all popularity polls and House
Speaker Jose de Venecia, the standard bearer of the ruling party.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines will have presidential, parliamentary and local
elections on May 11 this year.
</P>
<P>
President Fidel Ramos will step down on June 30 when his
six-year single term expires. 
</P>
</TEXT>
