<HEADLINE> Zhang Siqing, Vice-chairman of Ninth CPPCC National Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Following is a biographical
sketch of Zhang Siqing, who was just elected vice-chairman of the
Ninth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference:
</P>
<P>
Born in August 1932 in Luoyang, Henan Province, Zhang joined
Communist Party of China (CPC) in October 1952; started work in
March 1949, with an educational background of senior high school.
</P>
<P>
From 1952, served successively as clerk and investigator of
Central-South Section of Supreme People's Procuratorate, deputy
group head and assistant judge of Northeast China Work Team of
Supreme People's Procuratorate.
</P>
<P>
In 1955, was transferred to work in Yangtze River Water
Transport Procuratorate and later procurator of Hubei Provincial
Procuratorate. Worked in Public Security Department of Hubei
Province between 1969 and 1973, was deputy office director of
Higher People's Court of Hubei Province from 1973 to 1974, and
then became vice-president and president of Hubei Higher People's
Court, director of Provincial Public Security Department and
concurrently first political commissar of Hubei Armed Police Corps
and secretary of Provincial Political Science and Law Committee.
</P>
<P>
Promoted to deputy procurator general of Supreme People's
Procuratorate in 1985 and procurator general in 1993.
</P>
<P>
Was alternate member of CPC 13th Central Committee and member
of CPC 14th Central Committee, is member of 15th Central
Committees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
