<HEADLINE> Cameron Becomes IBF New Executive Director </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BIRMINGHAM, March 13 (Xinhua) -- David Shaw, the executive
director of the International Badminton Federation (IBF) announced
Friday he had resigned and was handing over to his successor Neil
Cameron of Scotland.
</P>
<P>
Shaw, who became IBF top official in 1992, decided to leave
three months earlier than expected.
</P>
<P>
The 52-year-old Cameron, a former IBF vice-president, has had a
long career with the sport including as being a player, coach,
umpire and international referee. 
</P>
