<HEADLINE> Zhao Puchu, Vice Chairman of CPPCC Ninth National Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Following is a biographical
sketch of Zhao Puchu, who was reelected vice chairman of the Ninth
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference here today.
</P>
<P>
Zhao, native of Taihu County, Anhui Province, born 1907,
received college education;
</P>
<P>
Is honorary chairman of Central Committee of China Association
for Promoting Democracy (CAPD) and president of Chinese Buddhist
Association.
</P>
<P>
Served 1928-38 as secretary of Shanghai-based Jiangsu-Zhejiang
Buddhist Union, secretary of Shanghai Buddhist Association; was
chief secretary of Buddhist Association based in Shanghai and and
a major sponsor for several social welfare institutions and took
charge of refugee reception during war against Japanese aggression
1938-45.
</P>
<P>
Was one of founders of Chinese Association for Promoting
Democracy and served as deputy director of CAPD Shanghai branch
1945-50; served as deputy head of Civil Affairs Department and,
concurrently, vice chairman of Committee for Production Relief of
East China Military and Administrative Commission, deputy director
of Political and Legal Work Committee of Shanghai Municipal
government 1950-53.
</P>
<P>
Served 1953-80 as vice chairman and chairman of China Buddhist
Association, secretary of Chinese Writers Association, vice
chairman of Chinese Calligraphers Association, vice chairman of
Sino-Japan Friendship Association, honorary president of Red Cross
Society of China.
</P>
<P>
After 1980, served as executive council member, member, vice
chairman and honorary chairman of CAPD Standing Committee,
chairman of CAPD Central Advisory Committee and vice chairman of
CPPCC National Committee.
</P>
<P>
Was member of first to third National Committees of CPPCC,
member of Standing Committees of Fourth and Fifth CPPCC National
Committees, vice chairman of 6th to 8th CPPCC national Committees,
and a deputy to 1st to 5th National People's Congresses. 
</P>
