<HEADLINE> Chinese National English Competition In Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The "21st Century Cup" top prize
in the Third National English Speaking Competition in Beijing
today went to Liang Limin, a student at Beijing Foreign Studies
University.
</P>
<P>
Liang will fly to London in May to participate in an
international English speaking competition.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-one students from major universities across the country
took part in the competition, which was judged by a panel of eight
Chinese and foreign English teachers or professors.
</P>
<P>
The contestants were asked to speak on "The East and the
West: Can We Live in Two Cultures?", and follow it with a
three-minute impromptu speech, and then a question and answer
session.
</P>
<P>
The competition is the highest level English contest in China
and is recognized internationally.
</P>
<P>
The first "21st Century Cup" competition was held by the
newspaper "China Daily" in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The third competition was sponsored jointly by China Daily, the
English-Speaking Union, the University of Cambridge Local
Examinations Syndicate, Times Publishing Group of Singapore,
British Airways, and the Kempinski Hotel Beijing Lufthansa
Center. 
