<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange (KLSE) closed higher Friday on strong buying
support of key blue chips but volume was thin in the absence of
fresh leads.
</P>
<P>
The Composite Index rose 9.93 points to 708.16, the Emas Index
added 2.09 points to 179.36, the Industrial Index was 13.41 points
higher at 1,275.77 and the second board index added 0.84 points to
179.95.
</P>
<P>
Gainers overwhelmed losers by 404 to 215, while 166 counters
were unchanged and 125 were untraded.
</P>
<P>
Friday's turnover fell to 167.393 million shares worth 407.566
million ringgit (106.69 million U.S. dollars) from 176.178 million
shares valued at 416.311 million ringgit (108.98 million U.S.
dollars) Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The main board's turnover was lower at 147.608 million shares
worth 362.200 million ringgit (94.816 million U.S. dollars) from
Thursday's 158.758 million shares valued at 363.250 million
ringgit (95.091 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The second board's turnover rose to 19.785 million shares worth
45.366 million ringgit (11.875 million U.S. dollars) from 17.420
million shares valued at 53.061 million ringgit (13.89 million
U.S. dollars) Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Off market business shrunk to 3.862 million shares worth 25.139
million ringgit (6.58 million U.S. dollars) from Thursday's 9.235
million shares valued at 29.617 million ringgit (7.753 million
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 6.309
million shares traded, industrial 11.164 million shares,
construction 13.770 million shares, trading/services 41.915
million shares, infrastructure projects 775,000 shares, finance
22.826 million shares, hotels 773,000 shares, properties 14.686
million shares, plantations 7.329 million shares, mining 756,000
shares, trusts 146,000 shares, closed/fund 480,000 shares and
loans 26.677 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said uncertainties on developments in Indonesia ahead
of the announcement of its Cabinet composition over the weekend
sent jitters to investors.
</P>
<P>
They added there were not much indications in the market as
investors were cautious over local corporate developments next
week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
