<HEADLINE> Ren Jianxin, Vice-Chairman of Ninth CPPCC National Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Following is a biographical
sketch of Jianxin, who was elected today vice-chairman of the
Ninth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC).
</P>
<P>
Ren was born in August 1925; a native of Xiangfen, Shanxi
Province; has been president of Supreme People's Court, secretary
of Committee of Political Science and Law under Communist Party of
China (CPC) Central Committee since 1992.
</P>
<P>
From 1946 to 1948, studied chemical engineering at Beijing
University; from 1948 to 1959, worked as a clerk for North China
People's Government, General Office of the Committee of Political
Science and Law under CPC Central Committee and Bureau of
Legislative Affairs under State Council.
</P>
<P>
In 1959, went to work at China Council for the Promotion of
International Trade (CCPIT) and served successively as director of
CCPIT's Legal Affairs Department, secretary general of Foreign
Economic and Trade Arbitration Commission, secretary general of
Maritime Arbitration Commission and CCPIT vice-president.
</P>
<P>
Served as vice-president of Supreme People's Court 1983-88, and
has served as president of Supreme People's Court since 1988.
</P>
<P>
Was member of 13th and 14th CPC Central Committees and member
of Secretariat of 14th CPC Central Committee.
</P>
