employment contract, introduced by the Sri Lankan Foreign
Employment Bureau and which is a must for Sri Lankans leaving the
country for employment, Senviratne told the sources before
departure.
</P>
<P>
The new deal has been accepted by many countries, but there are
still some gray areas and doubts mostly in the minds of certain
foreign employment agents, Senviratne said. However, there could
be amendments to suit the needs of individual countries and
adjustments would be made to accommodate the culture and standards
of different countries, he added.  
</P>
