<HEADLINE> Song Jian, Vice-Chairman of CPPCC National Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Following is a biographical
sketch of Song Jian, who was elected today vice-chairman of the
Ninth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC):
</P>
<P>
Song, born December, 1931 in Rongcheng, Shandong province;
joined Communist Party of China (CPC) in 1947; studied at a party
school and a school for training officials specializing in
industrial management in 1948 and Harbin Polytechnical University
next year#,followed by studies at Beijing Foreign Languages
Institute and Moscow Bauman Engineering Institute from 1953 to
1960.
</P>
<P>
From 1960 to 1965, served as deputy chief of Cybernetics
Research Office of Institute of Mathematics under Chinese
Academy of Sciences; after 1965, became deputy director and CPC
secretary of an institute, deputy head of Production Office and
vice-president of No.2 Institute of 7th Ministry of
Machine-Building Industry.
</P>
<P>
From 1981 to 1984, director and researcher of Beijing
Information Cybernetics Institute; vice-minister and chief
engineer of 7th Ministry of Machine-Building Industry;
vice-minister of Astronautics Industry. Appointed minister of
State Science and Technology Commission in 1985.
</P>
<P>
Since 1986, Song Jian has been state councillor and
concurrently minister of State Science and Technology Commission.
</P>
<P>
Alternate member of 12th CPC Central Committee and member of
13th to 15th CPC Central Committees; has been academician of
Chinese Academy of Sciences and academician of Chinese Academy of
Engineering.  
