<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chen Jinsheng, Vice-Chairman of CPPCC National Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Following is a biographical
sketch of Chen Junsheng, who was elected today vice-chairman of
the Ninth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC).
</P>
<P>
Chen, a native of Huanan County, Heilongjiang province; born
June, 1927; from 1946 to 1948, worked as member of Mass Movement
Group in Yilan County, Hejiang (today's Heilongjiang province) and
as member of Second Work Group of Provincial Government in charge
of organizational affairs Yidong County.
</P>
<P>
In 1949, served as personal secretary to first secretary of CPC
Heilongjiang Provincial Committee; from 1950 to 1957, worked in
Suihua, Fuyu and Keshan counties as head of CPC county committee
publicity department and secretary of CPC county committee
(Keshan);
</P>
<P>
From 1973 to 1984, worked as deputy director and director of
policy research office under CPC Heilongjiang Provincial
Committee, deputy director and director of General Office of
provincial Party committee, member of standing committee and
secretary-general of provincial Party committee, and concurrently
secretary of CPC Qiqihar Municipal Committee.
</P>
<P>
Worked as secretary (no first secretary then) and deputy
secretary of CPC Heilongjiang Provincial Committee in 1981-1984.
</P>
<P>
Served as vice-president of All-China Federation of Trade
Unions and deputy director of Rural Policy Research Office under
CPC Central Committee during 1984-85. Worked as secretary-general
of State Council from 1985 to 1988 and as a State councillor since
1988. Has been a member of 13th and 14th CPC Central Committees.
</P>
</TEXT>
