<HEADLINE> Li Guixian, Vice-Chairman of Ninth CPPCC National Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Following is a biographical
sketch of Li Guixian, who was elected vice-chairman of the Ninth
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC):
</P>
<P>
Born August, 1937; native of Gaixian County, Liaoning province;
started work in 1965, moved to study physical chemistry at
Mentzeliev Chemical Engineering Institute in Moscow the following
year; joined Communist Party of China (CPC) in 1962;
</P>
<P>
After working for a stint in a research institute under
Ministry of Public Security, he went to an electronic factory in
Jinzhou, Liaoning Province, in 1967, working up as worker,
technician, workshop chief, deputy director and chief engineer of
the factory; In 1977, appointed deputy director and chief engineer
of Jinzhou City Bureau of Electronics Industry.
</P>
<P>
Two years later, was promoted to be deputy director of Liaoning
Provincial Bureau of Electronics Industry.
</P>
<P>
In 1985, became secretary of CPC Liaoning Provincial Committee
and transferred to be secretary of Anhui Provincial Committee in
1986.
</P>
<P>
In 1988, appointed governor of People's Bank of China; has been
State Councilor from 1993. In 1994, became president of State
Administrative College.
</P>
<P>
Li Guixian was elected member of 12th, 13th, 14th and 15th
CPC Central Committees.  
</P>
