<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Institute to Be Established for Financial Stability </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, March 13 (Xinhua) -- An institute for financial
stability will be established under a joint initiative between the
Bank for International Settlements (BIS) and the Basle Committee
on Banking Supervision.
</P>
<P>
According to a BIS press release received here Friday, the BIS
institute, which is expected to begin its activities in the second
half of 1998, will be engaged in three principal activities:
</P>
<P>
-- The organization of high-level seminars directed by key
policy-making officials in central banks and supervisory agencies;
</P>
<P>
-- The provision of training on a regional basis for groups of
senior officials that implement policies;
</P>
<P>
-- Acting as a clearing house for the co-ordination and
provision of technical assistance by central banks and supervisory
bodies.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the institute is under consideration at a
time when Asia and other parts of the world have been affected to
a certain extent by a financial turmoil.
</P>
<P>
The institute will work closely with the principal supervisory
bodies, as well as with other international organizations engaged
in training functions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
