<HEADLINE> Chen Jinhua, Vice-Chairman of Ninth CPPCC National Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Following is a biographical
sketch of Chen Jinhua, who was just elected vice-chairman of the
Ninth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC):
</P>
<P>
Chen, male; born August, 1929; a native of Qingyang County,
Anhui Province; joined Communist Party of China (CPC) and started
work in February, 1949; graduated from People's University of
China and Beijing Television University.
</P>
<P>
Worked successively in Ministry of Textile Industry and
Ministry of Light Industry after founding of New China in 1949;
served as head of planning group of Ministry of Light Industry
from 1971 to 1976.
</P>
<P>
Worked in Shanghai from 1977 to 1983 and served successively as
Standing Committee member of CPC Shanghai Municipal Committee,
deputy Party secretary and vice mayor of Shanghai and director of
Shanghai Municipal Planning Commission.
</P>
<P>
Served as general manager of China Petrochemical Corporation
from 1983 to 1990; minister in charge of State Commission for
Economic Restructuring from 1990 to 1993.
</P>
<P>
Serving as minister in charge of State Planning Commission
since 1993.
</P>
<P>
Member of 14th CPC Central Committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
