<HEADLINE> Jing Shuping, Vice-Chairman of Ninth CPPCC National Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Following is a biographical
sketch of Jing Shuping, who was just elected vice-chairman of the
Ninth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC):
</P>
<P>
Jing, male; born July, 1918; a native of Shangyu, Zhejiang
Province; member of China Democratic National Construction
Association (CDNCA); graduated from St. John's University,
Shanghai; member of Standing Committee of Eighth CPPCC National
Committee; chairman of All-China Federation of Industry and
Commerce (ACFIC); president of China Minsheng Banking Corporation.
</P>
<P>
Served as deputy secretary-general and Standing Committee
member of ACFIC from 1957 to 1979; served successively as manager
of Real Estate Department and deputy general manager of China
International Trust and Investment Corporation, special consultant
for Foreign Investment Commission of People's Republic of China
and Ministry of Foreign Trade, vice-chairman of ACFIC, and deputy
secretary-general of CPPCC National Committee from 1979 to 1993.
</P>
<P>
Serving as Standing Committee member of Eighth CPPCC National
Committee, chairman of ACFIC and president of China Minsheng
Banking Corporation since 1993.
</P>
<P>
Member of Second to Fifth CPPCC National Committees and
Standing Committee member of Sixth to Eighth CPPCC National
Committees. 
</P>
