<HEADLINE> Cambodia's Auto Imports Drop in Second Half of 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia's auto imports
dropped in the second half of 1997 by more than 65 percent from
the first half, according to statistics from the Finance Ministry
Friday.
</P>
<P>
About 2,000 vehicles were imported in the period as against
5,800 for the first six months, the statistics said.
</P>
<P>
Customs House Port Deputy Chief Kim Nguon said the majority of
the imports, mainly from the United States and Japan, are
second-hand, because of money problems. "It's easier to sell
second-hand cars," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
