<HEADLINE> Li Ruihuan Reelected Chairman of Ninth CPPCC National Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan was reelected chairman
of the Ninth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC) this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The result came from the Fifth Plenary Meeting of the First
Session of the Ninth CPPCC National Committee held here this
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan is a Standing Committee member of the Political
Bureau of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee. He
was elected chairman of the CPPCC National Committee for the first
time in March 1993.
</P>
<P>
The CPPCC is the most extensive patriotic united front
organization in China, with its main functions to exercise
political consultation, democratic supervision and participation
in and deliberation of state affairs.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, today's plenary meeting elected Ye Xuanping and 30
other people vice-chairmen of the Ninth CPPCC National Committee,
and Zheng Wantong secretary-general of the Ninth National
Committee, and 290 people members of the Standing Committee of the
Ninth National Committee.  
</P>
</TEXT>
