<HEADLINE> International Environmental Symposium Closes in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 13 (Xinhua) -- A Sino-European Environmental
Technology Symposium closed today in Shanghai, China's largest
commercial center.
</P>
<P>
About 100 Chinese and European experts spent five days
discussing international cooperation in environmental protection
and high-tech developments for treating waste gases and wastewater.
</P>
<P>
The experts also visited a number of waste disposal facilities
and Shanghai's environmental research center.
</P>
