<HEADLINE> Xinhua Weekly World News Schedule </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The following is a list of major
world news events from March 15 to 21:
</P>
<P>
March 15  -- India's new parliament convenes in New Delhi after
</P>
<P>
 national elections.
</P>
<P>
-- International arbitrators make decisions on
</P>
<P>
 status of Bosnian town of Brcko.
</P>
<P>
-- Japanese Prime Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto visits
</P>
<P>
 Indonesia to hold talks with President Suharto.
