<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gansu Province Trying to Protect Farmland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Gansu Province in northwest China
has successfully stemmed its rapid loss of precious farmland
caused by a construction boom.
</P>
<P>
Though farmland continues to be acquired for new projects, the
acreage of provincial farmland rose slightly last year because of
the reclamation of 7,533 hectares and the conservation of other
farmland.
</P>
<P>
A highland province, Gansu long has been suffering from
inadequate and low-quality farmland. To save land, the province
has worked out very strict measures concerning its use. Last year,
the province resolved 56,000 land-abuse cases.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
