<HEADLINE> Haikou Bonded Zone Attracts More Foreign Investments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The Haikou Bonded Zone in the
capital of the island province of Hainan has attracted 73
foreign-funded enterprises and 209 domestic enterprises in the
past five years.
</P>
<P>
The Haikou Bonded Zone began operations in 1993. About 400
million yuan has been put into infrastructure construction
projects such as paving 2.2 million cubic meters of roads and
building 210,000 square meters of workshops and storehouses.
</P>
<P>
Since late in 1997, the zone has attracted 55 projects with
nine foreign-funded enterprises having more than 610 million U.S.
dollars in registered capital. Four enterprises completed
investment and operation work in a year with total investments
exceeding 1.3 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, the zone has nearly 600 million yuan in sales, with
more than six million yuan paid in taxes. The bonded zone has
developed international trade, export processing and storage
exhibition.  
</P>
</TEXT>
