<HEADLINE> Northwest Region More Accessible to Information </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The recent completion of two
communication projects has made it possible for people in Xinjiang
Uygur Autonomous Region to have easy access to telephones and
information.
</P>
<P>
This northwestern ethnic region had difficulty in contacting
the outside world through long-distance telephones, especially
during peak hours. But now, it has more than 2,000 satellite
telephone lines, compared with only nine in 1986 when it began
satellite communications.
</P>
<P>
The region has set up four ground satellite stations, as well
as 26 digital mini-stations, forming a satellite information
network linked to most other provinces, autonomous regions and
municipalities.
</P>
<P>
The recently completed satellite communications projects cost
more than 20 million yuan, with equipment imported from the United
States.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang will expand the capacity of existing digital telephone
lines this year, and add four ground satellite stations, local
sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
