<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Flocks of Endangered Pheasants Found in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Two flocks of brown-eared
pheasants, an endangered species, have been found at Lingshan
Mountain in the western suburbs of Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Zoologists say that the species of brown-eared pheasants has
only been discovered in north China's Shanxi and Hebei provinces,
and like the giant panda and golden monkey, it is under state
first class protection.
</P>
<P>
Last October zoologists found several big birds they had never
seen in Beijing. The birds were identified as brown-eared
pheasants. The zoologists traced the pheasants and found two
flocks with a total number of 43 birds.
</P>
<P>
Zoologists say brown-eared pheasants, one meter in length and
weighing 2-to-3 kilograms, run fast and live in pairs. They eat
plant roots, seeds and insects. They mate in spring, and every
female lays 8-to-10 eggs.
</P>
<P>
The newly found pheasants came from Shanxi Province, said
zoologists. Related departments are taking measures to protect
them.
</P>
<P>
Lingshan Mountain has a variety of vegetation; and 116 species
of birds live on the mountain.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980313.0230 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian President to Announce New Cabinet Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President Soeharto who
has been re-elected to a seventh term in office is expected to
announce the members of a new cabinet on Saturday, an official
said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Head of the presidential household, M. Basyuni told a press
conference that the new ministers will take their oath on March 16
at the State Palace.
</P>
<P>
Basyuni also said that the head of state, who will be
accompanied by Vice President B. J. Habibie, is scheduled to chair
the first meeting of the new cabinet on the following day.
</P>
<P>
Basyuni did not give details about the number of the new
cabinet for the 1998-2003 term.
</P>
<P>
Soeharto was re-elected on Tuesday to his seventh term of
office by the People's Consultative Assembly, the country's
highest legislative body.
</P>
<P>
According to the original schedule, the new cabinet will be
formed at the end of this month.
</P>
<P>
Sources close to the palace said the hasty formation of the
cabinet reflected the president's deep concern over the lingering
economic crisis in the country.
</P>
<P>
Since July last year, Indonesia has been facing spiraling
inflation, growing unemployment and other serious economic,
financial and social problems caused by a rapid decline of the
rupiah currency.
</P>
<P>
At present, the rupiah is trading at about 10,000 against the
U.S. dollar, compared with 2,400 per dollar in July last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
