<DOCNO> XIE19980313.0231 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzania-Zambia Railway Revenue Increases by </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 13 (Xinhua) - The Tanzania-Zambia Railway
Authority (TAZARA) generated 12.682 billion Tanzanian Shillings
(nearly 20 million U.S. Dollars) during the 1997/98 fiscal year,
a 28.1 percent increase compared with the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Tanzanian Minister for Communications and Transport William
Kusila said in a statement Friday that the increase was achieved
mainly by improved passenger and cargo services.
</P>
<P>
"For example, TAZARA managed to ferry 778,530 passengers
during the first half of the 1997/98 fiscal year compared to
686,022 during a corresponding period in 1996/97," he said.
</P>
<P>
The minister, who doubles as the chairman of the Ministerial
Council for TAZARA, said that the Authority has managed to
increase its engine capacity from 30 percent to 57.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
TAZARA has rehabilitated damaged wagons and increased the
number of wagons from 1,122 to 2,280 which suffice the demand, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The 1860-km railway, built by the Chinese government in an aid
program in the 1970s, has survived the recent destructive floods
linked to the EL Nino rains which have paralyzed the Central
Railway linking the coast in the East to the Tanganyika Lake in
the West. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980313.0232 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northwestern Chinese Areas Cooperating in Developing Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Five provinces and autonomous
regions in northwestern China will cooperate in developing
regional tourism in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi, Gansu, Ningxia, and Qinghai provinces, and the
Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region all have their own individual
characteristics and attractions like cultural relics of Shaanxi,
the Dunhuang frescos of Gansu, the temples of Qinghai, unique
lakes of Ningxia, and the Tianshan mountain of Xinjiang.
</P>
<P>
The new Eurasian continental bridge has brought further
opportunities for tourism development in northwest China. In 1998,
the five provinces and regions will cooperate on tourist routes,
developing tourist products, and improving tourism facilities.
</P>
<P>
Special trains and planes will be added to link tourism
attractions, like the Urumqi-Liuyuan passenger train and the
Xi'an-Dunhuang air route. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
