<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Approves 67 Export Processing Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The Export Processing Zones
Authority of Zimbabwe has approved 67 projects over the past
year, and 24 of them are now operational, according to the
Zimbabwe News Agency Ziana Friday.
</P>
<P>
Investment Executive of the authority Patrick Sibanda Thursday
told participants attending a one-day workshop in Bulawayo,
organized by trade promotion body Zimtrade, that Zimbabwe was far
ahead of many African countries in establishing export processing
zones.
</P>
<P>
Sibanda would not say how much the 67 projects were valued at,
but in January the authority had approved 62 projects worth more
than 1.4 billion Zimbabwean Dollars (about 80 million U.S.
Dollars).
</P>
<P>
He said among the projects approved were a 10,000 square
meters vegetable dehydrating plant in Stapleford outside Harare,
four fruit and vegetable canning factories in the capital, and
two shoe-making projects and a timber processing company in
Bulawayo, the second largest city of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
