<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wellington, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
rallied on Friday, prompted by buying in Telecom and Fletcher
Challenge shares.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 30 points higher at 2299 with a turnover
of nearly 80 million dollars (46 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Telecom shares jumped 25 cents to 855 cents. Three of the four
Fletcher Challenge shares were also firmer with Building climbing
10 cents to 394 cents, Forest up 3 cents to 130 cents and Paper
gaining 2 cents to 248 cents. However, Fletcher Energy went
against the higher trend, easing 5 cents to 605 cents.
</P>
<P>
Other main leaders also closed stronger. Air New Zealand lifted
3 cents to 203 cents. Brierley Investment and Carter Holt Harvey
each rose 2 cents to 112 cents and 260 cents respectively. Lion
Nathan picked up 8 cents to 440 cents.
</P>
<P>
Overall, there were 54 rises and 33 falls.  
</P>
