<HEADLINE> Qingdao to Hold Foreign Trade Fair, Beer Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The '98 Qingdao Foreign Trade
Fair and the Eighth International Beer Festival will be held
in Qingdao in east China's Shandong Province in July.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has decided to treat foreign-funded
enterprises in the province as Chinese ones, properly open the
domestic market to foreign investors' products, and unify the
service charge standards for both overseas and domestic investors,
according to the International Trade News.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has also adjusted its policy of
attracting foreign investment so as to encourage foreign investors to
participate in the property transfers of state-owned
enterprises, the development of high-tech and basic industries, and
infrastructural construction.
</P>
<P>
During the fair, international electronic products and
household electrical appliances will be exhibited and a seminar on
beer-making technology and equipment held. 
</P>
