<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australia Donates 578,000 U.S. Dollars to Laos </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Australia would provide 578,000
U.S. dollars to increase public awareness of unexploded mines and
ammunition in Laos, Australian Foreign Minister Alexander Downer
said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Downer said the money would go towards a nationwide program in
Laos to alert school children, their families and ethnic
minorities about the danger of unexploded mines.
</P>
<P>
Downer said the money would also support a program aimed at
giving the government of Laos the ability to manage the clearance
of mines and unexploded ammunition.
</P>
<P>
"Australia is one of the leading contributors to international
land mine clearance programs," Downer said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Since March 1996 the Australian government has provided 12
million U.S. dollars for demining assistance and the government
expects to commit 66 million U.S. dollars to demining initiatives
in the decade to 2005.
</P>
<P>
Downer said Australia's donation would also be used to train
people in Laos in disaster preparedness. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
