<HEADLINE> Technology Market Booming in Chinese Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Beijing's technology market had
a record transaction volume of 5.4 billion yuan (650 million
U.S. dollars) in 1997, an increase of 18.56 percent over 1996.
</P>
<P>
The figure is also the top one in the country, today's Beijing
Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, 2.07 billion yuan (249 million U.S. dollars), or
38 percent, are involved in contracts for technological
development, and the remaining cover technological transfers,
consultation and services.
</P>
<P>
Beijing has 260,000 scientific and technological workers and
great potential for technological development. Through the
technology market, according to the report, 5,394 technological
items were used for industrial development; 3,011 for social and
economic development; 1,926 for communications, telecommunications
and energy resources; and 714 for education and public health
promotion in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The paper reported that industrial enterprises are the leading
buyer on Beijing's technology market. In 1997, industrial
companies from across the country bought 6,215 technological
items, involving 2.5 billion yuan (301 million U.S. dollars) or 46
percent of the total transaction volume.
</P>
<P>
According to the paper, 179,400 technological items were
involved in transactions during the last decade, with a combined
value of 31.195 billion yuan (3.75 billion U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
