<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Steffi Graf retired from her
semi-final match with a strained hamstring in the Evert Cup tennis
tournament in Indian Wells on Thursday, putting American Lindsay
Davenport one match away from defending her Evert Cup crown.
</P>
<P>
Third seed Graf, playing in only her second tournament after
nine months recovering from knee surgery, suffered the injury in
the fifth game of the third set.
</P>
<P>
Second seed Davenport led 6-4, 4-6, 4-2 when Graf called it a
night.
</P>
<P>
Graf, who has won 21 Grand Slam singles titles in her career
and held the world No. 1 ranking for a total of 374 weeks, said
she didn't know if she would be ready for the Lipton Championships
in Key Biscayne next week.
</P>
<P>
Davenport, who will take on the winner of Friday's second
semi-final between world No. 1 Martina Hingis and eighth-seeded
Venus Williams. 
</P>
