<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Medical Operation Performed on Ming Dynasty Corpse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The corpse of a Shanghai
resident during the Ming Dynasty (1368-1644) received a medical
operation on Wednesday, an autoposy conducted by Shanghai and Hong
Kong doctors, the Shanghai-based Wenhui Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
The corpse, unearthed in Shanghai in 1994, was that of Gu
Chongli, a celebrity and a high-ranking official who died at the
age of 81. It was the best preserved ancient corpse ever found in
Shanghai, China's biggest city in east China. Examination of the
body showed that the internal organs were intact, which will aid
further research.
</P>
<P>
After a half-hour operation a 49-gram heart, two halves of the
brain, and lobes of the lung were removed from the body.
</P>
<P>
"The autoposy study of this ancient corpse can tell us a lot,"
said Xu Yongqing, an expert on ancient corpses with the Shanghai
Natural Museum. The research will be of great significance for
ancient pathology, medical archeology, ancient environmental
science and medical history, Xu said.
</P>
<P>
"It can provide answers to such questions as why the corpse
didn't rot for 400 years; which disease he died of; which diseases
he suffered in his old age; and even provide information on his
living environment through analysis of the air in his lungs," Xu
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980313.0251 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand Sees Exports Surge in February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's exports increased
sharply by 93 percent in February compared to the same month last
year, strengthening the country's record of a trade surplus for
six consecutive months.
</P>
<P>
According to figures from the Customs Department here Friday,
exports in February totaled 216.51 billion baht (about 5 billion
US dollars), up 93.08 percent, while imports increased 17.72
percent to 165.58 billion baht (3.9 billion dollars), resulting in
a trade surplus of 50.9 billion baht (1.1 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
However, the department did not provide figures in US dollar.
The baht has plunged from 25 against the dollar in the first half
of last year to about 43 now.
</P>
<P>
The department said that for the first two months of 1998 the
country recorded a total trade surplus of 96.38 billion baht (2.2
billion dollars), compared to 81.22 billion (1.9 billion dollars)
in the previous four months.
</P>
<P>
Computers and associated equipment, garments, rubber and rubber
products are the top export earners in February.
</P>
<P>
The government has targeted export growth in dollar terms for
at least 7 percent this year to 62.6 billion dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
