<HEADLINE> Bangladesh, Bhutan Plan Land Route via India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh and Bhutan are planning
to open a land route through India to promote trade between the
two countries, Foreign Ministry officials said.
</P>
<P>
The government proposed the route through Nakuagaon in Sherpur
district, some 150 kilometers north of here, and Dalu in Bhutan,
the officials were quoted as saying recently by one of the
country's leading English newspapers, The Daily Star, on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Bhutanese authorities agreed to the proposal in principle,
they said.
