<HEADLINE> Italian FM: Kosovo Should Participate in Negotiations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Kosovo's ethnic Albanians should
show their willingness to negotiate with Belgrade if the situation
is to improve in the Serbian province, Italian Foreign Minister
Lamberto Dini said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Demands for independence by ethnic Albanians, who make up 90
percent of the two million people in Serbia's Kosovo province,
have met with violent repression. Dini said however the local
population is also '``partly to blame for the crisis.''
</P>
<P>
Kosovo exploded in violence within the past two weeks and
nearly 80 people have been killed.
</P>
<P>
Dini said a solution to the crisis depends on a constructive
approach by the people in Kosovo, who could see international
sympathy rapidly evaporate if they do not do their part.
</P>
<P>
He said the Serbian government was showing signs of a
willingness to negotiate and "we are waiting for the other side to
do the same."
</P>
<P>
The minister said he had talked with Serbian President Milan
Milutinovic, who gave signs of his willingness to comply with
these demands.
</P>
<P>
His failure to comply would lead to "more severe measures,"
Dini warned, adding that if Kosovo withdraws from the dialogue
with Belgrade, it will be blamed for the deterioration in the
situation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
