<HEADLINE> Chinese Iron-Steel Giant Has Record Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANSHAN, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The Anshan Iron and Steel
Conglomerate (Angang), China's largest, in Liaoning Province, had
a record 889,000 tons of exports last year.
</P>
<P>
Angang has more than 70 trade partners worldwide and ship
certification from Norway, Germany, Britain, France and the
Republic of Korea for its ship-building section steel and steel
plates, a major part of its international sales.
</P>
