<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 12 (Xinhua) -- American Andre Agassi, bidding
for his third title of this year, knocked out third-seeded
Australian Pat Rafter to reach the quarter-finals of the 2.45
million U.S. dollars Champions Cup tennis tournament in Indian
Wells on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The 6-3, 3-6, 6-2 victory provided Agassi with a concrete
