<HEADLINE> Italy, Ethiopia Sign Defense Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Italy and Ethiopia signed a defense
cooperation agreement here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The agreement, signed by Italian Defense Minister Nino
Andreatta and Ethiopian Deputy Defense Minister Gebre Tsadkan,
covered military training and other forms of aid, including
defense supplies for the Ethiopian air force and army, said an
Italian defense ministry communique.
</P>
<P>
According to the communique, the aim of the agreement is to
develop Ethiopia's capability for contributing to peace-keeping
missions of the United Nations and the Organization for African
Unity.
</P>
<P>
The agreement may also be extended to include assistance for
the African country's military police and security forces.
</P>
<P>
Italian defense ministry officials noted that the agreement
testified to the Italian interest in ``contributing to regional
security and stability in the strategic Horn of Africa region.''
</P>
</TEXT>
