<HEADLINE> Overseas Investment for Agriculture Increases in Northeast China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, March 12 (Xinhua) -- An increased amount of overseas
investment has helped the industrialization of agriculture in
Dalian, northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The city added 41 overseas-funded agricultural projects last
year, bringing the total number to 491. The agricultural projects,
which account for 7.2 percent of its overseas-funded businesses,
have 250 million US dollars worth of contractual overseas
investment from 21 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
Up to 80 percent of the overseas funds will be spent on
orchards, aquiculture, and the processing of farm produce.
</P>
<P>
Exports of overseas-funded agricultural enterprises were worth
180 million US dollars last year, accounting for 10 percent of
exports of overseas-funded businesses in the city.
</P>
<P>
Dalian now has nearly 7,000 overseas-funded enterprises and is
the leading city in northeastern China in use of overseas
money. 
</P>
</TEXT>
