</P>
<P>
LONDON -- Government or state leaders from the 15 European
Union (EU) countries and their counterparts from 11 EU applicant
central and eastern European countries agreed to promote
cooperation in various fields at Thursday's European Conference
held in London.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the final press conference after the one-day
meeting, British Prime Minister Tony Blair said that this first
ever pan-European conference was a "truly historical" moment by
bringing countries from all over Europe together.
</P>
<P>
"The whole objective of the conference is to create a stable,
secure and prosperous Europe," Blair said
earlier.(BC-UK-EU-Conference)
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- Defense researchers in Britain have developed a
cheap, safe and simple method of burning landmines without having
to explode them.
</P>
<P>
The firework-like device, named FireAnt, can be operated by a
battery from a distance of 50 meters, the New Scientist magazine
reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It works by directing a jet of flame at landmines from a few
centimeters away, searing a hole in the casing, igniting the
detonator before it can set off the mine and incinerating the high
explosive so that it simply burns off without exploding.
</P>
<P>
FireAnt torches the mine for around 25 seconds, leaving the
explosives to burn themselves out in a few minutes, the magazine
said. (BC-UK-Landmines)
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan, praising the
role played by Moscow in resolving the Iraqi weapons inspection
crisis, said on Thursday that he would visit Russia early next
month.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters at the National Press Club in Washington,
Annan said, the main purpose of his visit is to show that the
world community stand together to deal with the weapons inspection
crisis.
</P>
<P>
"I'll be in Moscow beginning of April, and again to show that
we all stand together on this Iraqi crisis, and send a message to
the Iraqi leadership that they've signed an agreement and the
whole international community intends to hold them to its
fulfillment," Annan said.(BC-Annan-Russia)
