<HEADLINE> China's Treasury Bond Sales Brisk </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- China's banking system sold more
than 70.3 billion yuan (8.5 billion U.S. dollars) in state
treasury bonds between Feb. 20 and March 11, according to
statistics from the People's Bank of China, the central bank.
</P>
<P>
The amount represented more than 58.6 percent of the scheduled
issue of 120 billion yuan in certificate bonds, the sale of which
will last till Oct. 31, China Securities reported today.
</P>
<P>
In another analysis, 48.1 billion yuan was in three-year bonds
and 22.2 billion yuan in five-year bonds, the daily newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
It attributed the brisk buying to the slow pace of the stock
market in recent days and low returns on treasury bonds in the
secondary market.
</P>
<P>
China issued treasury bonds valued at 241.2 billion yuan in
1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
