<DOCNO> XIE19980313.0305 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ecuador Cocoa Exports Dip 60 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Ecuador's cocoa exports in the
first two months this year fell by 60 percent over 1997 to eight
million U.S. dollars, a report from the Ecuador Cocoa Producers
National Association said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The report attributed the export plunge to the El Nino
phenomenon. It said torrential rains arising from the El Nino
phenomenon knocked out flowers and favored the growing of monilla,
a fungus that covers the fruit of the cocoa tree, which caused
a sharp drop in cocoa output this year.
</P>
<P>
The slump in cocoa exports, the report added, is expected to
continue in the coming months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
