<HEADLINE> Teahouses Gaining Popularity in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Teahouses are replacing karaoke
and disco halls, bars and cafes are becoming the favorite places
for Beijingers to visit during their spare time.
</P>
<P>
There are now 40 teahouses in Beijing, and the number is
expected to reach 100 by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
Local teahouses include three groups: small ones that just
provide tea; traditional-style teahouses; and large ones with
multiple functions such as entertainment and food.
</P>
<P>
A modern teahouse manager, Gu Xiaoming, attributed the
popularity of teahouses to their ease of operation and low
cost. Teahouses also provide a more simple and elegant environment
which people seem to enjoy, the manager added.
</P>
<P>
Actress Dong Yunling said she loves drinking tea. She often
visits teahouses, she said, and has a tea room in her apartment.
</P>
<P>
She stressed that drinking tea helps build better moral
character in people.  
</P>
</TEXT>
