<HEADLINE> South China City to Improve Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Nanning, the capital of south
China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, will put 1.9 billion
yuan into improving the environment this year.
</P>
<P>
A city government official says that the money will be used in
sewage treatment, planting of trees and grass, and building of
scenic spots in Nanning for the region's 40th anniversary.
</P>
<P>
The city government will emphasize industrial waste treatment
and improvement of the air quality of Nanning. By this November, a
sewage treatment plant will be in operation in the city's new
development zone, and another one will be completed for the
control of pullution of the Nanhu Lake in the city.
</P>
<P>
Nanning will plant about 232,000 square meters of grass along
the Yongjiang River. 
</P>
