</P>
<P>
-- Australia is preparing to spend an extra 19 million U.S.
dollars on emergency aid for Indonesia and to send military
aircraft to distribute food, amid concerns over the impact on
social stability of spiraling prices and shortages of essential
items in the Southeast Asian country.
</P>
<P>
