</P>
<P>
-- Australian Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade officials
criticized those in the Department of Defense preparing evacuation
plans for 15,000 Australians in Indonesia in the event of major
breakdown of law and order, saying they are confident that such a
rescue will not be necessary.
</P>
<P>
The Age:
</P>
<P>
-- Australian Resources and Energy Minister Warwick Parer has
been exempted by Prime Minister John Howard from key elements of
the ministerial code of conduct as it emerged that the mining
company in which Parer holds shares gained 90 million U.S. dollars
during his first year as minister.
</P>
<P>
The Australian Financial Review:
</P>
<P>
-- High-profile Funds Manager Bankers Trust Australia is ready
to swoop on Hayman Island for about 67 million U.S. dollars,
completing a series of deals that has seen most of Queensland
state's resort islands change hands over the past year. 
