<HEADLINE> Canada Condemns Attack on Burmese Refugee Camp </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Canada condemned the attack on a
Burmese refugee camp near Mae Sot on the Thai-Burma border,
Foreign Affairs Minister Lloyd Axworthy said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Burmese military forces were reported to destroy Wednesday the
Huay Kalok refugee camp in Thailand. Four people were killed, 39
wounded, and thousands of refugees left without shelter.
</P>
<P>
"Canada is appalled by the cross-border attack on Burmese
refugees in Thailand, a painful reminder of the Burmese
government's continued abuse of its citizens," Axworthy said in a
news release.
</P>
<P>
"In addition to transgressing international boundaries, the
attack represent an unacceptable violation of basic human rights,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
The Burmese ambassador here has been called in by Canada's
Department of Foreign Affairs and International Trade to be
advised of its condemnation of this act, the release said.
</P>
<P>
Axworthy also welcomed the Thai government's assertion that it
will do its utmost to prevent such attacks in the future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
