<BODY>
<HEADLINE>   EU Unsatisfactory With French World Cup Ticket Offer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 12 (Xinhua) -- A senior European Commisison
official said Thursday the French World Cup organizers had not
made a satisfactory offer to distribute more tickets to supporters
from outside the host country.
</P>
<P>
Karel van Miert, European commissioner for competition
policies, made the remark while addressing a European Parliament
session in Strasbourg.
</P>
<P>
The commissioner said that the French organizers had offered to
distribute 50,000 of the 160,000 remaining tickets to the national
soccer associations.
</P>
<P>
There are in all 2.5 million tickets available for this year's
cup tournament that kicks off on June 10.
</P>
<P>
"We are not yet satisfied by what we have been offered by the
organizers," van Miert told the European legislators.
</P>
<P>
The European Commission, the executive body of the 15-nation
European Union, said that under EU laws of fair competition, the
way the tickets for this summer's World Cup tourney have been
distributed discriminates against people from outside France.
</P>
<P>
But the commission admitted that it was powerless to retrieve
the tickets already sold out.
</P>
<P>
The European Commission and the French organizers were expected
to reach a settlement on making more tickets available for
non-French supporters.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of the French organizing committee met European
Commission officials last week in Brussels and they are meeting
again this week in an effort to reach any settlement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
