<HEADLINE> Dow Ends 16 Points Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Most of the market indicators on
the New York Stock Exchange held firm on Thursday except for the
benchmark index of the Dow Jones industrial average which fell
16.19 to close at 8,659.56.
</P>
<P>
After soaring a total of 108 points in two previous days, the
Dow dipped 64 points in morning trading amid profit-taking.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 stock list rose 1.48 to 1,069.95 and
the NYSE composite index rose 0.60 to 557.90. Both set a close
record for the third day.
</P>
<P>
The technology heavy Nastaq composite index jumped 7.21 to
1,764.06.
</P>
<P>
NYSE advancing shares narrowly led decliners with 1,493 up,
1,411 down and 545 unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Trading volume declined to 593.38 million shares from 653.32
million shares on Wednesday, according to preliminary figures.
</P>
<P>
On smaller companies' line, the Russell 2000 index rose 0.66 to
467.78 and the American Stock Exchange was up 0.52 to 714.45.
</P>
<P>
The market performance was coupled with a Commerce Department
report that U.S. retail sales rose 0.50 percent in February
following a 1.0 percent growth in January.
</P>
<P>
The figures were considered positive to show that consumer
spending, a major component of economic output, posted a healthy
beginning in 1998. 
</P>
