<HEADLINE> Canadians Names B.C. Best Place to Live </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Nearly one in three Canadians say
they would move to British Colombia (B.C.) province to live if
they could, according to a new poll released Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Residents in B.C. also agree that their province is the best
place to live in Canada, with 76 percent giving it top marks,
higher than anywhere else in the country.
</P>
<P>
The weather, the scenery and natural surroundings are what make
B.C. the number one place to live and retire, the poll found.
</P>
<P>
The survey, conducted in December by the Angus Reid Group for
the Royal Bank of Canada, interviewed 1,500 Canadians on
everything from housing and day care to weather and retirement.
</P>
<P>
The results are considered accurate within 2.5 percent, 19
times out of 20.
</P>
<P>
It is the latest look into quality of life issues as the new
millenium approaches, the bank said in a release. 
</P>
</TEXT>
