<HEADLINE> World PC Market Forecast to grow 13.4 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The global personal computer
market is expected to grow 13.4 percent in 1998 and reach a volume
of 90.6 million units, the U.S. market researcher International
Data Corp. reported.
</P>
<P>
That's down from a 15.2 percent growth in 1997 when 79.9
million units were sold, it said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Solid demand for PCs in regions such as the U.S., Western
Europe and Latin America continue to offset weakness in many Asian
markets, the company said.
</P>
<P>
It expects the United States market to expand 15.4 percent,
down from 19 percent last year. 
</P>
