<HEADLINE> Chief Executive of Hong Kong Visits Lyons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The Chief Executive of Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) of China, Tung Chee Hwa,
paid a visit to the French industrial city of Lyons on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Tung was received by the Mayor of Lyons, Raymond Barre, and
visited the "Magally" automatic wide gauge metro subway of the
conurbation of Lyons, as well as the International Agency for
Research on Cancer which is based in the French city, said a
member of the Hong Kong delegation.
</P>
<P>
Tung, who is on a three-day visit to France since Wednesday,
will be received by President Jacques Chirac on Friday before
flying back to Hong Kong. 
