<HEADLINE> French Enterprises to Reinforce Presence in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The French government encourages
enterprises of the country to reinforce their presence in Hong
Kong despite the financial crisis which has hit the Southeast Asia
region, said French Foreign Ministry spokesman Yves Doutriaux on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Making a brief statement on the visit to France by the Chief
Executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region of China,
Tung Chee Hwa, the spokesman said that French enterprises in Hong
Kong will be prepared for the future and a resumption of economic
growth in that region.
</P>
<P>
He recalled that Tung met with French businessmen on two
different occasions Wednesday and Thursday in Paris to establish
constructive dialogue with the French corporate.
</P>
<P>
He also said that Tung has attained the objective of his visit
to France, which is very important for both France and Hong Kong.
</P>
